Poem.villanelle:
Thin films of superconducting materials, a high resistance in the normal state,
InO and NbTiN, NbN, TiN are studied with great debate;
A spatially inhomogeneous state can arise due to strong disorder,
The evolution of electromagnetic response measured by microwave resonators.

The quasiparticle density of states changes with increasing disorder;
We describe the measured response with a heuristic model which contains an effective pair breaking parameter.
Scanning tunneling spectroscopy is used to compare the assumed DoS;
For the lowest disordered film we find affirmative results but for the most disordered film a strong discrepancy. 

A spatial inhomogeneous superconducting state appears as we increase disorder; 
This signals the breakdown of a model based on average properties. 
It's clear that thin films of superconducting materials must be studied further; 
To understand their electromagnetic response and its evolution with disorder. 

We must investigate these materials from both application and fundamental points of view; 
To comprehend their behavior and how it changes with increasing disorder. 
The study of thin films of superconducting materials is still ongoing,  
As we strive to better understand their electromagnetic response.

Poem.limerick:
A thesis on the Tibetan Plateau,
For monitoring solar radiation was great;
It requires a high resolution,
To account for clouds and terrain's composition;
So that the budget can be updated daily, without any debate.

Poem.villanelle:
The Belt and Road Initiative, a plan for global peace,
Will spark debate and bring both doubt and relief.
Though many questions linger, it's set to increase
The chance of collaboration, a new belief.

At Khorgos Gateway, the research takes its start;
To bridge the gap between local and global art.
It seeks to facilitate interaction through design;
A symbiosis of old and new to impart. 

Five goals are set for this International Centre; 
To share culture and knowledge in this place so fair. 
An evaluation framework is proposed to see 
How well the concept can be transferred there. 

This work is meant to spark interest in all; 
For further research on BRI’s grand call. 
Though fraught with risk, it’s sure to succeed or fail; 
Depending on how it’s executed spatially on the local scale.

Poem.limerick:
A reduction in drag or fluid resistance
Provides potential energy savings, no question;
The mechanism behind the effect,
Remains largely unresolved yet;
But dimples can offer a strong suggestion.

Poem.villanelle:
The benefits of reduced drag are clear, with savings to the environment and economy;
Though its working mechanism is still unclear, dimpled surfaces can be key.
PIV and PISFV show spanwise oscillations, which cause a converger-diffuser type flow;
This novel aerodynamic surface could help us save energy, don't you know?

Dimples have advantages over other means of passive flow control;
They're shallow and require no maintenance or cleaning in whole.
This research provides data that helps us understand their mechanics too;
It's clear that they have potential to reduce drag and make us anew. 

Although there are still questions about the working of dimpled surfaces, 
We can see the potential for energy savings if we look at the forces. 
The interaction between them leads to alternating spanwise excitations; 
Any reduction in vehicle drag has obvious benefits for all nations. 

With this research we can strengthen our understanding of dimpled surfaces; 
The turbulence created by them could lead to substantial energy savings. 
Their use could be advantageous for industry competitiveness and more; 
Any reduction in vehicle drag or fluid resistance is worth exploring for sure.

Poem.sonnet:
The Ganges and Brahmaputra, two of the world's mightiest streams,
Bring water to Bangladesh with their great downstream dreams.
The distributaries they form, though ever-changing in flow,
Are key to fresh water for the South-West and Central regions below.

But when the dry season comes and water levels start to fall,
Some distributaries disconnect from their parent rivers, a threat to them all.
Data acquisition is often not possible for preliminary designs or early stages of projects;
Morphological changes occur too quickly for data to be collected. 

A physics-based numerical model is used instead of field data; 
It can simulate the river system accurately enough for an initial assessment instead. 
Analysis of offtake systems are made before setting up the model, 
To identify causes of closure and propose remedial measures as well. 

Dredging upstream during recession is one measure proposed; 
Though it needs to be applied regularly, it could prevent closure imposed. 
Other measures such as submerged erodible weirs or training walls were tested too; 
But none proved effective in maintaining flow in the distributary through and through. 

This thesis has developed a methodology that overcomes lack of data availability; 
With this tool it's possible to simulate realistic scenarios of offtake closures quickly. 
By using this approach engineering measures can be assessed without much resources needed; 
For Bangladesh's complex river system, this is a great success indeed!
